Job Description:

  Pick up quantities from tender drawings and compile as standard Bill of Quantity to review on contract administration.
  Prepare quotation, project costing and vendor sourcing.
  Prepare sub-contract documents, progress claim, variation order and final account.
  Check and put up recommendation on sub-contractor’s bill for payment.
  Reply to incoming sales enquires.
  Any adhoc duties as assigned.


Job Requirements:

  Candidates must possess at least a Diploma/ Bachelor Degree in Quantity Surveying/ Construction Management or equivalent.
  Candidates without relevant experience are welcome to apply.
  He/ She may need to visit sites as and when the situation requires.
  Able to communicate effectively bilingually (English and Mandarin).
  Willing to learn, meticulous and committed to accomplish datelines.
